<br>
So instead of removing Detect magic, a completely useless spell, they just replaced it with true north, a mostly useless spell. <br>
<br>
I say mostly useless, because sometimes it is nice to know you're going straight north, for finding /loc's and stuff, since only one coordinate will change.<br>
<br>
The lull/pacify/soothe etc line works fine.  I've used it all over, sebilis, howling stones, city of mist, and others.  And it does lower the aggro range enough to normally split up a pull.<br>
<br>
It doesn't work reliably, so just don't rely on it.  There's a lot of situations where your group _could_ handly 4 mobs at once, but it would be in your best interest to split them up and take them two at a time.  Root and mez will eventually break, but if you get a successful lull type spell in, they WILL stay at their home until you, or someone else pulls them.<br>
<br>
Page 1 spell? no way... completely useless though? nope not that either.  Just don't EXPECT it to work... it's just a nice bonus when it does. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wulfherehausakliufr>Wulfhere Hausakliufr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 893<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/22/02 10:16:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15351.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> lull resist rates hurt tha spell line</span><hr size=1> Was along time ago that the resist rates on lull and fear spells got silently nerfed. They've been unnerf since but ne'er been tha same for lulls. Failure rate on them went from like 40% to 99% failure for a few weeks. Now they be aboot 60-70% failure.<br>
