Evac doesn't work when you're being Gfluxed to the ceiling and harm touched, btw. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugaladril1961.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galadril1961</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 316<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/24/02 6:13:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15351.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why did I ever bother spending money on this spell?</span><hr size=1> I use the soothe from DW vambraces quite often. And they help increase single pulls enough that I consider it worthwhile. Four things will result, in roughly equal shares: the mob resists and comes alone anyway, the mob doesn't resist and you single pull a different one, the mob resists but doesn't agro, the mob resists and agro's along with it's friends.<br>
<br>
Clicking the vambraces is a no-lose scenario though, it will give you some single pulls that you wouldn't otherwise have gotten, and doesn't decrease your chances of single pulls when it is resisted. It also costs no mana and doesn't use up a spell slot.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, casting the spell with mana (often 2-3 times if mob resists but doesn't agro) is not worth it. It eats alot of mana and uses a spell slot without much much of anything to show for it. Your other pull spell whether it be cancel/nullify magic or cease has more range and so if there is operating room available you are probably better off using range and level to get your single pull. I prefer cease to cancel/nullify magic for pulling, as it it does double duty for interrupts and saves a spell slot. <p><b>
