<br>
I found another use for it.<br>
<br>
I was doing &quot;run&quot; tests (comparing running speed versus JBoots, horses, etc.)  To eliminate all sources of variation other than the actual speed buff, I wanted to run across exactly the same test course every time.<br>
<br>
Starting in the same spot was easy enough, I could use a landmark on the ground and center myself on it every time, but making sure that I was running in exactly the same direction every time, and not, say, 3 degrees off for each attempt was a problem.<br>
<br>
Or at least it would have been a problem without True North.  I cast True North before each trial run, and that way I could be absolutely certain that I was starting in the same spot, *and* running in exactly the same direction every time (and thus over the exact same terrain). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufolokthedwarf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Folok the Dwarf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 142<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/24/02 2:38:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15351.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.gigahosts.com/~c1003/aimicons/buddyicons/Alf/alfphoneani.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why did I ever bother spending money on this spell?</span><hr size=1> Pacify is an odd line of spells. Sometimes, if it is resisted, the mob will not attack. i have used it a few times to split pulls in Velks. If u cast and pull and get adds its most likely the spell wore off. It does not last very long and is very random. VI said that we will never be able to see, &quot;Your pacify spell has worn off.&quot; They stated that it would be an over balance. <p><b>Folok Solot</b><BR>
